Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Thinly slice the @portobello mushrooms{2}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a garlic press). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(finely chopped) (stalks and all).

Pour half the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} into a #bowl{} with the @olive oil{1%tsp} for the dressing and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together and set aside until ready to serve.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the saucepan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together. Set aside, off the heat.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add all the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and cook, stirring occasionally, until the mushrooms are browned and the bacon is golden, ~{6-7%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Once browned, reduce the heat to medium-low and add the onion. Cook, stirring frequently, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the remaining balsamic vinegar and cook until evaporated, ~{1%minute} more.

Pour the @water{150%ml} for the sauce into your frying pan and stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}.

Increase the heat and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer until reduced, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{99%g} until well combined, then bring back to the boil and add a good grind of pepper. Remove from the heat.

Add the cooked pasta to the sauce along with three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and three quarters of the parsley.

Stir everything together. Taste and add more salt and pepper if needed.

Spoon your mushroom penne into #bowls{} and sprinkle the remaining cheese and parsley on top.

Add the @wild rocket{20%g} to the balsamic dressing and toss together. Serve on top of the pasta finished with another good grind of pepper. Enjoy!